The paper proposes a deep learning approach for brain lesions detection using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of a novel operation unit, which suggests a focus on developing new neural network architectures (cs.AI). The evaluation of the proposed approach on benchmark datasets indicates a focus on machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of Magnetic Resonance Images (MRI) suggests a focus on medical imaging (cs.MM), and the use of deep learning techniques suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
